'''Simon Hunt''' (born 1963 in [[Chester]]) is a retired [[England|English]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who played in both the UK and Sweden. He is currently head of international scouting at [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]].<ref name = "Ipswich sign defender Balkestein">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/i/ipswich_town/7457679.stm|title=Ipswich sign defender Balkestein|accessdate=23 February 2009|date=16 June 2008|publisher=BBC}}</ref><ref name = "International Scout Appointed">{{cite web|url=http://www.itfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10272~1329520,00.html|title=International Scout Appointed|accessdate=23 February 2009|date=16 June 2008|publisher=Ipswich Town}}</ref>

==Career==
===Playing career===
Beginning his career at [[Wrexham F.C.|Wrexham]], Hunt made over 100 appearances for the Welsh club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/wrexham/wrexham.htm|title=WREXHAM : 1946/47 - 2007/08|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Database}}</ref> Hunt later played in Sweden for [[IF Elfsborg]], [[IK Brage]] and [[GAIS]]<ref>http://www.gais.se/Fotboll/gais.nsf/0/E944680F249DF80AC1256F16003A6409</ref>.

===Coaching career===
After retiring as a player, Hunt has managed Swedish sides [[IK Brage]]<ref>http://www.ikbrage.se/index.php?newspage=63&open=3</ref> and [[Kalmar FF]], and has scouted for English sides [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]], [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] and [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]] and Scottish side [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/sport/football/article570542.ece|title=Glory Hunt|accessdate=23 February 2009|date=25 September 2005|author=Neil White|publisher=The Sunday Times}}</ref> Hunt returned as a scout to [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] in June 2008.<ref name = "Ipswich sign defender Balkestein"/><ref name = "International Scout Appointed"/>

